{"search_data": "Central PM Modi Minority Scholarship Scheme for 5 Crore Alpsankhyak Students (Padho-Badho) PM Modi Minority Scholarship Scheme 2019-2020 for 5 crore (2.5 crore girls) alpsankhyak students including pre-matric, post-matric, merit-cum-means scholarships, Padho Badho campaign & madrassa modernization programme to launch for minorities, bridge courses for drop-out school girls of minority communities \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902In order to ensure socio-economic and educational empowerment of minorities particularly girls through 3Es \u2013 Education, Employment & Empowerment, govt. will start PM Modi Minority Scholarship Scheme. Various scholarships including pre-matric, post-matric, merit-cum-means etc would be provided to 5 crore students in next 5 years. These scholarships would include more than 10 lakh Begum Hazrat Mahal girls scholarship in upcoming 5 years for economically weaker sections.Prime Minister\u2019s Scholarship Scheme for Minorities would create an atmosphere of healthy inclusive growth by eliminating the disease of communalism and appeasement politics. Bridge courses from reputed educational institutions will start for drop-out school girls belonging to minority communities.PM Madrassa Programme 2019-2020All the madrassa teachers across the country will be given training by various institutions in mainstream subjects such as Hindi, English, Maths, Science and Computer. PM Madrassa Programme 2019-2020 would enable these teachers to impart mainstream education to the madrassa students. The madrassa programme will be launched in the month of July 2019.#WATCH Union Minister of Minority Affairs Mukhtar Abbas Naqvi: Madrasas which are there in large number across the country are to be connected with the formal education & mainstream education so that those children in Madrasas can also contribute in the development of the society pic.twitter.com/wHPO9zed4N\u2014 ANI (@ANI) June 11, 2019Under Pradhan Mantri Jan Vikas Karyakram (PMJVK), govt. is already constructing schools, colleges, ITIs, polytechnics, girls hostels, gurukul-type residential schools and common service centres in areas devoid of infrastructure.Padho Badho Awareness Campaign by PM ModiThe central govt. will also launch \u201cPadho Badho\u201d awareness campaign to encourage education particularly girls from minority communities. The main focus is on those areas where people does not send their children to schools due to socio-economic reasons.Padho Badho campaign will primarily focus on girls and will include Nukkad Natak (street plays), short films and cultural programmes. This campaign is going to be launched in 60 minority concentrated districts of the country in the 1st phase.The Indian govt. would also provide free coaching for competitive exams like central and state administrative services, banking services, staff selection commission, railways. All the people belonging to EWS category from minority communities like Muslims, Christians, Sikhs, Jains, Buddhists and Parsis would be eligible.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/modi-government-announces-scholarships-to-5-crore-minority-students-in-next-5-years-1546833-2019-06-11  at  "}